From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: ntdll/unix: spoof AMD64 as native machine in SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures

Pre-Windows-on-ARM installers (notably IK Multimedia TONEX 1.12 via Inno
Setup 6.4.2) call IsWow64Process2 to detect the native machine and exit
early with "wrong Windows version" if it's ARM64 — even though FEX-Emu
would happily translate their x86_64 PE code at load time.

Patch 0009 added AMD64 to supported_machines (so the supported list
includes x64). This patch separately spoofs AMD64 as the *native* entry
in the SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures reply. The actual native
(server-side supported_machines[0]) remains ARM64, so wine's internal PE
loader keeps finding aarch64-windows DLLs in system32/. The lie is purely
in what we tell user-mode code via IsWow64Process2 / GetSystemInfo paths.

The real native (ARM64) is still listed in the reply, just as a non-
native wow64 entry — so callers that do enumerate supported machines
still see ARM64 listed.

diff --git a/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c b/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
@@ -3866,18 +3866,42 @@
         memset( machines, 0, len );

-        /* native machine */
-        machines[0].Machine = supported_machines[0];
+        /* fex-pivot: on ARM64 with FEX, the REAL native is ARM64 but we want
+         * IsWow64Process2 / SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures to report
+         * AMD64 as native — pre-Windows-on-ARM installers (IK TONEX 1.12 /
+         * Inno Setup 6.4.2) reject the OS if native_machine=ARM64, even
+         * though FEX-Emu would translate their x86_64 code transparently.
+         * Wine's internal loader keeps using the real native_machine
+         * (server-side supported_machines[0]=ARM64) so aarch64-windows
+         * system DLLs still load — only the user-facing reply lies. */
+        USHORT presented_native = supported_machines[0];
+        if (supported_machines[0] == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64)
+        {
+            for (i = 1; i < supported_machines_count; i++)
+            {
+                if (supported_machines[i] == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64)
+                {
+                    presented_native = IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64;
+                    break;
+                }
+            }
+        }
+
+        /* native machine (presented to caller) */
+        machines[0].Machine = presented_native;
         machines[0].UserMode = 1;
         machines[0].KernelMode = 1;
         machines[0].Native = 1;
-        machines[0].Process = (supported_machines[0] == machine || is_machine_64bit( machine ));
+        machines[0].Process = (presented_native == machine || is_machine_64bit( machine ));
         machines[0].WoW64Container = 0;
         machines[0].ReservedZero0 = 0;
-        /* wow64 machines */
-        for (i = 1; i < supported_machines_count; i++)
+        /* wow64 machines (skip the one we promoted to native, demote the
+         * REAL native to a wow64 entry so callers still see ARM64 listed) */
         {
-            machines[i].Machine = supported_machines[i];
-            machines[i].UserMode = 1;
-            machines[i].Process = supported_machines[i] == machine;
-            machines[i].WoW64Container = 1;
+            ULONG out = 1;
+            for (i = 0; i < supported_machines_count; i++)
+            {
+                if (supported_machines[i] == presented_native) continue;
+                machines[out].Machine = supported_machines[i];
+                machines[out].UserMode = 1;
+                machines[out].Process = supported_machines[i] == machine;
+                machines[out].WoW64Container = 1;
+                out++;
+            }
         }
         ret = STATUS_SUCCESS;
